ce:section.ce:para:
The absorption spectra have been measured in the range 200–500 nm through UV–Visible spectrometer (Perkin Elmer, Waltham, MA, USA). Steady state fluorescence spectra have been recorded on a (EDINBURG Instrument) FL920 spectro-fluorometer with Xenon lamp source (Fig. 1
                     ). Time resolved fluorescence spectroscopy has been carried out by Picosecond Pulsed Laser (model EPL-300 nm, S/N −024/360/03/11) of pulse width 775.2 ps and band width 9.6 nm (Fig. 2
                     ). Anton Paar (Litesizer) 500™ instrument has been used to measure the values of zeta potential, conductivity and electrophoretic mobility. TEM image and SAED pattern have been obtained from the instrument HR-TEM Model: Tecnai G2 20 S-TWIN.
